{
  "texts": [
    "The same can possibly be done at the journal level to explore whether journals with high market shares of ChatGPT publications obtain increased citation metrics or other reputational effects in the long run.",
    "Another limitation of our bibliometric analysis is that based on bibliometric data collected and analyzed at one point in time.",
    "Therefore, it is difficult to make predictions about the future evolution of the research literature on ChatGPT.",
    "Donthu et al. (2021, p. 295) point out that \"bibliometric studies can only offer a short-term forecast of the research field\" and highlight that it is important to be careful when making assertions about its future importance and impact.",
    "This is especially the case regarding research on ChatGPT since it has been rapidly expanding, and there is much uncertainty related to its future evolution and trajectory."
  ]
}